column1: if I do say so myself
if I may be so bold
in the flower of one's youth
in the wink of an eye
down the road, not across the street
quicker than a minnow can swim a dipper
over the hills and far away
with one arm tied behind one's back
with one hand tied behind one's back
with one's thumbs up one's ass
back to the old drawing board
every day of the week and twice on Sunday
every day of the week and twice on Sundays
never in a month of Sundays
faster than a minnow can swim a dipper
for a song and a dance
four score and seven years ago
until one is blue in the face
like a bull in a china shop
like a bump on a log
a day late and a dollar short
any day of the week and twice on Sunday
any day of the week and twice on Sundays
as if one's life depended on it
as if one's life depends on it
as near as makes no difference
this side of the black stump
through the wrong end of the telescope
